						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Two fragments of a slab standing in the Taluk Office.</hi></p>						

						<p>Jagadēkamalla II—A.D. 1139.</p>						

						<p>This record is fragmentary. The details of the extant portion of date are the cyclic year <hi rend="bold">[Siddhārthi], Pushya, śu. 5, Thursday.</hi> This corresponds to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1139, December 27,</hi> the weekday, however, being <hi rend="bold">Wednesday.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription seems to register a gift of land to god Nāgēśvaradēva. It mentions Kētōja and Nāgōja and also two Jaina preceptors Nandi-bratīs11a and Tējōnidhi-bratīśa. </p>						

						</summary>
